    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "> Wouldn't it be sensible to remove the usage of deprecated functions in a minor release first?\r\n\r\nWe want to guarantee a smooth upgrade between minor releases. This means we don't want to do any breaking changes (such as removing a function) in a minor.\r\n\r\nThat is what majors are for: making breaking change and removing things we want to stop supporting.\r\n\r\nAlso note that removing the preset is part of the planned breaking changes for 5.0",
